Porosity from Density: Volumetrics
Description: Plain and simple.`Beware that this formula only works if the input density is always between the matrix and fluid density.
Formula: (c0 - den) / (c0 - c1)
Variable.0.Type: Density
Variable.0.Name: Input density
Constant.0.Name: Matrix density
Constant.0.Description: The average density of the rock material itself.`Therefore, the density for posority 0.
Constant.0.Typical Range: 2.2`2.9
Constant.1.Name: Fluid density
Constant.1.Description: The average density of the fluid.`Therefore, the density for 100% posority.
Constant.1.Typical Range: 0.5`1.2
!
Density from Porosity: Density
Description: Plain and simple.`Beware that this formula only works if the input porosity is always between the 0 and 1.
Formula: ( 1 - por ) * c0  +  por * c1
Variable.0.Type: Porosity
Variable.0.Name: Input porosity
Constant.0.Name: Matrix density
Constant.0.Description: The average density of the rock material itself.
Constant.0.Typical Range: 2.2`2.9
Constant.1.Name: Fluid density
Constant.1.Description: The average density of the fluid.
Constant.1.Typical Range: 0.5`1.2
!
